olitics, he paints a vivid portrait of public servants who care more about political power and personal gain than the public good. By recounting events that he witnessed firsthand in the Garden State, he provides dramatic illustrations of ills that afflict American politics nationwide. As he identifies five main forms of soft corruption, Schluter diagnoses the state government’s ethical malaise, and offers concrete policy suggestions for how it might be cured. Not simply a dive through the muck of New Jersey politics, Soft Corruption is an important first step to reforming our nation’s political system, a book that will inspire readers to demand that our elected officials can and must do better. Visit: www.softcorruption.com (http://www.softcorruption.com)   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Jan 2021) 0aCampaign fundszNew Jersey. 0aConflict of interestszNew Jersey. 0aMisconduct in officezNew Jersey. 0aPatronage, PoliticalzNew Jersey. 0aPolitical corruptionzNew Jersey. 0aPolitical culturezNew Jersey. 4acorrupt. 4acorruption. 4acronies. 4acrony capitalism. 4acurrent affairs. 4aelection. 4aethics. 4agarden state. 4agovernment. 4agreed. 4alaw. 4alegislature. 4alobbyist. 4anew jersey politics. 4anew jersey. 4anews. 4anj law. 4anj legislature. 4anj politics. 4anj. 4apolitical corruption. 4apoliticking. 4apolitics. 4apublic official. 4apublic servant. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package 2017z978311066609040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081358619940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813586199423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813586199.jpg  a978-3-11-066609-0  RUP eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL